topIssues.title: op-batcher: stay in sync with op-node rollup config
topIssues.author: joshklop
topIssues.body:
Upon startup, the op-batcher fetches the rollup config from the op-node over RPC. It never fetches the rollup config after that.

https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/40554025301e5adde90191adba6ad432e185fa50/op-batcher/batcher/service.go#L238-L253

This is problematic during hard forks when the system deposit transaction format changes: an outdated rollup config will result in an error from which the batcher cannot recover without restarting.
https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/40554025301e5adde90191adba6ad432e185fa50/op-batcher/batcher/driver.go#L310
```
failed to parse L1 info deposit tx from L2 block: data is unexpected length: 178
```

The op-batcher should stay in sync with the op-node's rollup config.

One solution is to fetch the rollup config if the above error is hit. An alternative is to for the batcher to restart itself automatically.

topIssues.body:

**Bug Description**
https://github.com/tyler-smith/go-bip39 is no longer hosted on GitHub, and thus is no longer available as a dependency. 

However, it is still referred on the code. 

https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/op-chain-ops/devkeys/hd.go#L8
https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/go.mod#L62


It's still in proxy.golang.org, but when you don't use GOPROXY, `go mod tidy` breaks.

https://proxy.golang.org/github.com/tyler-smith/go-bip39/@v/v1.1.0.info


**Steps to Reproduce**

On a clean clone, 
```
export GOPROXY=off
go mod tidy
```

I think this command made me notice this broken dependency. 
```
 go clean -cache -modcache -testcache && go mod download
```

topPRs.title: ci: Prepare for kona prestate verification
topPRs.author: Inphi
topPRs.body:
Add support for cannon-kona prestate build in the monorepo. Depends on updates to the standard prestates in the superchain-registry - https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/superchain-registry/pull/1144

### Testing
```bash
cd op-program
scripts/build-prestates.sh
go run ./prestates/verify/verify.go \
  --input temp/states/versions.json  \
  --expected ../../superchain-registry/validation/standard/standard-prestates.toml # get this from the above pr
```

fixes https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/17283

topPRs.title: SaferSafes audit fixes 2
topPRs.author: alcueca
topPRs.body:
## Audit Fixes

- **`configureTimelock` allows a zero delay** ([Cantina](https://cantina.xyz//code/4c27cc57-83c2-4e6d-89ba-9cc7a1ca4e0c/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/safe/TimelockGuard.sol?preview=code#comment-c970dfd9-8b5e-41c3-942c-7d840bd20136))  
  While not really wrong, we can achieve the same thing by disabling the Timelock, which gives us a single path to document and maintain instead of two. Commit: [0cda697](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/0cda697be878c320e5fd423aef2faf8bca867a7d)

- **`fallbackOwner` as `owners[0]`** ([Cantina](https://cantina.xyz//code/4c27cc57-83c2-4e6d-89ba-9cc7a1ca4e0c/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/safe/LivenessModule2.sol?preview=code#comment-71c5fed7-ba0b-4873-8b5e-b056564f96b4))  
  Because we don't check the success of `swapOwner`, this has no impact, but it should be documented. Commit: [ec527e6](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/ec527e6e0ebc65363a933e69327226f472e1ffe5)

- **`configureLivenessModule` and `configureTimelock` are inconsistent with the invariant that the timelock delay must be twice the liveness response period** ([Cantina](https://cantina.xyz//code/4c27cc57-83c2-4e6d-89ba-9cc7a1ca4e0c/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/safe/SaferSafes.sol?preview=code#comment-b9ec9c08-1982-431c-ad6d-585e5d1a2132))  
  Fixed by requiring the Timelock to be enabled on `configureTimelockGuard`. Commit: [b436d76](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/b436d76fd6906dce63745dec8e692206b0d37635)

- **Enforce `fallbackOwner != safe` in `configureLivenessModule`** ([Cantina](https://cantina.xyz//code/4c27cc57-83c2-4e6d-89ba-9cc7a1ca4e0c/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/safe/LivenessModule2.sol?preview=code#comment-a1451236-f9bf-4a85-87ac-9a21909098a1))  
  Commit: [0e475c7](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/0e475c7e7c4c7d54df217435cfefdb51faa37eb5)

- **Enforce that the guard is enabled as a requisite for `configureTimelockGuard`** ([Cantina](https://cantina.xyz//code/4c27cc57-83c2-4e6d-89ba-9cc7a1ca4e0c/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/safe/TimelockGuard.sol?preview=code#comment-c970dfd9-8b5e-41c3-942c-7d840bd20136))  
  Commit: [b436d76](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/b436d76fd6906dce63745dec8e692206b0d37635)

- **`txHash` is only indexed in the `ScheduledTransaction` events, but not on the other events**  
  Commit: [003bbff](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/commit/003bbffcdb0255c1241e446edf357769e90b00d0)

---
